over phone]

06:50.750 --> 06:54.049
No, I heard everything. Yeah,
no, Clay would love to meet you.

06:54.100 --> 06:55.408
He would.

06:55.450 --> 06:57.236
We just, with his schedule,
we can't really...

06:57.280 --> 07:00.408
Of course.

07:00.460 --> 07:03.679
Of course, we will make it work
if we can.

07:03.720 --> 07:06.985
I love you.
Okay, bye.

07:07.030 --> 07:11.239
You do not know what
you're getting yourself Into.

07:13.300 --> 07:16.337
On your right is our state
of the art media complex,

07:16.390 --> 07:19.211
where students produce
everything from news broadcasts

07:19.260 --> 07:22.343
to virtual reality
experiences.

07:22.390 --> 07:24.176
Up ahead is our
campus coffee shop.

07:24.220 --> 07:26.176
Karaoke and pizza

07:26.220 --> 07:28.745
every Tuesday.
Yeah, I'm sure
we can do that.

07:28.790 --> 07:30.223
It seems like our girls
are fast friends, huh?

07:30.270 --> 07:33.797
Yeah.
Nice campus, huh?

07:33.840 --> 07:36.400
Of course this is
a safety for my Katie.

07:36.450 --> 07:39.180
She's really hoping
for Yale or Princeton.

07:39.240 --> 07:40.582
But between
you and me,

07:40.630 --> 07:42.279
her GPA's
only a 4.1.

07:42.330 --> 07:44.104
4.1?

07:44.150 --> 07:47.802
Yeah, better than perfect,
not enough. What a world.

07:47.850 --> 07:50.193
Uh, what about
your daughter?

07:50.250 --> 07:52.673
JASON: Uh... Whatever
choice she makes,

07:52.730 --> 07:54.425
I'm there for her.

07:54.470 --> 07:56.938
She's happy, I'm happy.
Excuse me.

07:56.990 --> 07:58.685
Uh, great talking to you.

07:58.730 --> 08:00.994
I kind of love it here.

08:01.040 --> 08:03.292
Is this a safety school for you?

08:03.350 --> 08:05.568
Safety? I should know
what that is, right?

08:05.610 --> 08:08.215
It means it's a lock
that I'll get in here.

08:08.270 --> 08:11.615
Okay. All right, yeah.
It's nice. I like it.

08:11.660 --> 08:13.651
You know what, hey,
I support any choice you make.

08:13.710 --> 08:15.439
All right?

08:15.490 --> 08:17.094
Just, you know, you end up
at a frat party,

08:17.140 --> 08:18.573
I may have to gather up the boys

08:18.620 --> 08:20.224
and crack some skulls,
you understand?

08:20.280 --> 08:21.929
I'm not joking.

08:24.850 --> 08:26.329
Work?

08:26.370 --> 08:27.405
Yup, work.

08:27.460 --> 08:28.415
Hmm.

08:28.460 --> 08:30.109
Remind me not to pick a career

08:30.160 --> 08:32.242
that can turn my life
upside down at any moment

08:32.290 --> 08:35.509
and screw up my kid's day.

08:35.550 --> 08:38.428
Right.
It's fine.

08:38.470 --> 08:41.428
I'll come back with Mom
to see the rest of the school.

08:41.470 --> 08:42.459
JASON:
Okay.

08:58.400 --> 08:59.742
I'll have what
he's having.

09:04.450 --> 09:06.498
I don't think
she likes you.

09:06.540 --> 09:08.360
That's unfortunate.

09:08.410 --> 09:10.583
That's predictable.

09:10.630 --> 09:12.541
Nobody likes an
arrogant American

09:12.590 --> 09:14.069
who thinks she can
stroll in here

09:14.110 --> 09:16.931
and intimidate us locals.

09:16.990 --> 09:18.503
It's bad manners.

09:18.550 --> 09:21.018
MANDY:
I apologize for offending

09:21.080 --> 09:22.468
your Victorian
sensibilities.

09:25.650 --> 09:27.424
Graham Kowit.

09:29.780 --> 09:31.293
I don't know who that is.

09:31.350 --> 09:33.045
American DEA agent,

09:33.090 --> 09:34.432
went missing a few weeks ago,

09:34.480 --> 09:37.472
and I'm guessing you know
where to, Fausto.

09:44.140 --> 09:45.960
Only friends use my name.

09:46.020 --> 09:48.750
Be careful, it can be
terribly unhealthy

09:48.800 --> 09:52.327
for a foreigner to poke her nose
in the wrong places,

09:52.370 --> 09:53.496
in my world.

09:53.540 --> 09:56.498
My advice:
focus on your own health.

10:21.490 --> 10:23.617
Davis, saw you
working out early.

10:23.660 --> 10:26.481
It's a little
out of the ordinary.

10:26.530 --> 10:28.998
What's out of the ordinary
is that you weren't tied up

10:29.060 --> 10:31.051
with a bunch of strippers
when we got paged.

10:31.100 --> 10:32.362
JASON: Strippers.OTHERS: Ooh!

10:32.410 --> 10:33.923
SONNY:
Hey, don't be judgy, Davis.

10:33.980 --> 10:36.403
Okay, nothing wrong
with bunches of strippers.

10:36.460 --> 10:38.587
Okay, the swarm seems best.

10:38.630 --> 10:40.063
JASON: Whoa, whoa, whoa,
excuse me there,

10:40.110 --> 10:43.159
Mr. GQ, no, no, no, you do
not get to comment, okay?

